## Reference

### Branch model

```
{{branch_feature_prefix}}<task-id> ──(free merge, no template)──→ {{branch_dev}}{{#has_dev_branch}}   ← staging/test sandbox{{/has_dev_branch}}
{{branch_feature_prefix}}<task-id> ──(PR + template required)───→ {{branch_main}}  ← protected
```

- **`{{branch_feature_prefix}}* → {{branch_main}}`**: open a PR — [.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md](.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md) loads. Self-merge is allowed; the discipline lives in honestly filling the protocol-status field.{{#has_dev_branch}}
- **`{{branch_feature_prefix}}* → {{branch_dev}}`**: merge freely for testing. No PR template, no review.
- **No `{{branch_dev}} → {{branch_main}}` flow** — `{{branch_dev}}` is a throwaway sandbox.{{/has_dev_branch}}

### Forbidden actions

| Don't | Why |
|---|---|
| `git commit --no-verify` | Bypasses the format/test verification at commit points. The protocol depends on this. |
| `git push --force` to `{{branch_main}}` | Destroys history that other contributors may have synced. |
| Skipping `{{verify_format}}` / `{{verify_test}}` at a `> ✋ Commit point` | The brief promises both pass at every commit. Don't lie to future you. |
| Editing code under {{paths_forbidden_inline_or}} without an active task brief | Unless explicitly marked **out-of-protocol** in the PR, every code change must trace back to a task brief. |

### Useful one-liners

```bash
./harness status                     # what task is in flight?
./harness implement <task-id>        # resume a paused task (also switches to its branch)
./harness end                        # archive a finished task
./harness remember "<text>"          # save a long-term decision/convention to MEMORY.md
./harness curate-memory              # quarterly MEMORY.md cleanup
./harness help                       # full command list
```

### Where to look

- **Project map** ("which files do I edit to change X?"): [{{paths_architecture_doc}}]({{paths_architecture_doc}}) *(maintained by this repo)*
- **Protocol spec** (the rules every AI assistant follows): [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md)
- **Step-by-step coordinator/implementer flow**: [.harness/workflow.md](.harness/workflow.md)
- **Cross-task knowledge** (conventions, decisions, pitfalls): [.harness/MEMORY.md](.harness/MEMORY.md)
- **Triage rules** (small change vs full task): [.harness/triage.md](.harness/triage.md)

### Getting unstuck

- `./harness status` shows current state.
- See [Path A troubleshooting](#troubleshooting-path-a) for AI-driven flow issues.
- Project-specific gotchas, if any, are documented under [Project-specific pitfalls](#project-specific-pitfalls) below.
